Hiya
Morning.
Are you happy with these top 5 takeaways from last week's RFA workshop:

Insider Risk in 2021

 

  • 'Unstructured' communications data is an untapped resource in which most risk lies in the form of malicious intent from bad actors, through to inappropriate language and conduct from employees. This data ranges from emails, voice calls, direct messages through to social media, and more.
  • Not knowing your people, clients and investors pose both a regulatory and reputational risk to firms.
  • Firms are most concerned about the loss of business and reputation due to misconduct and miss-appropriateness from their leadership, employees, clients, and investors due to the push for accountability and an ESG focus from wider social, political and cultural influences.
  • The directive of 'setting the tone from the top' is high up the agenda for the FCA, set by the SYSC handbook with a continued push for personal accountability.
